body.description: Enfamil ProSobee Infant Formula is a soy-based Infant Formula with plant-sourced protein that is naturally easy on sensitive tummies. It is suitable for infants with lactose intolerance and a dairy-free alternative to milk-based formula. Also perfect for families with special dietary needs (vegetarian or Kosher). Enfamil ProSobee helps reduce fussiness and gas sometimes caused by milk-based formulas. *Enfamil is the #1 pediatrician recommended brand of Infant Formula - QuintilesIMS, using the ProVoice Survey fielded from October 1, 2016 to September 30, 2017. **Enfamil Infant Formula that had 0.32% of total fatty acids as DHA.

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Easy to use
reviews.reviewText: Easy to use in a pinch. We buy these for when we travel. My sister recently used them when she was travelling in her camper van (when making and storing powdered formula was more of a hassle).Tip: write the open date on the lid. It keeps for 48 hours.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 1, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Perfect for travel or use when water is not available
reviews.reviewText: Ok I’ll be honest I purchased these for my granddaughter’s 72 hour bug out bag because they were ready to feed and no water needed to be added. These have come close to their expiration date so I gave them to my daughter to use up. I recommended her using these when mixing with baby cereal in fear that the taste wouldn’t be the same as the powder but my granddaughter didn’t stick her nose up at it she couldn’t tell the difference from the RTF or the powder. I will purchase another case of these to have for her bug out bag. Definitely recommend if you live in a hurricane zone, wildfires or tornados. And let’s be honest we live in a day and age that it’s not just natural disasters we should be preparing for!!! Man can be more destructive than nature!! Keeping a case of these on hand for emergencies is just being a smart move in my opinion!!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 8, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Nice Lactose Free Formula
reviews.reviewText: This formula does have a strange smell compared to milk-based formulas, but it is a good option for a lactose free formula. This formula helped with my son's digestive and gas issues, even when the Enfamil Gentlease wouldn't. The product arrived quickly and in good condition.

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Easy and newborn loves it
reviews.reviewText: I needed something to supplement breastfeeding while sore nipples healed. I took this to the hospital for my labor. My newborn loved it, drinks it right out of the fridge. No stomach issues, almost no spitting up, no powders to mix etc. As a vegan it is a great and convenient option.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 23, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Great but caused constipation
reviews.reviewText: My 6 week old was really gassy and fussy with cows milk formula. We switched to this and it really was so much better on his stomach until it constipated him. We started doing half and half but that’s just not sustainable for us. We went back to the cows milk and he’s right back to being super gassy and fussy. We’re going to keep searching for a formula that works for his sensitive belly. Possibly goats milk based formula will help!
